{
  "text": "We cloned a 1.9-kb genomic fragment (Ϫ1744 to ϩ156) of the c-FLIP gene and inserted it into the luciferase reporter construct (pGL3). Transient transfection of this reporter plasmid into PC3 cells resulted in an approximately 6-fold higher level of luciferase activity in the presence of AR than in the absence of AR ( Fig. 2A, left panel) . This promoter was also androgen inducible in the AR-positive LNCaP cells ( Fig. 2A,  right panel) . These results suggest that the cloned c-FLIP genomic fragment contained functional AREs, which we then further mapped using a collection of deletions ( Fig. 2A, left panel) . The deletion from the 5Ј-end to Ϫ48 did not affect AR-induced luciferase activity, whereas deletion from the 3Ј-end to ϩ20 resulted in its complete loss, indicating that the functional AREs localized within the region from ϩ20 to ϩ156 of the c-FLIP promoter. The alignment of the ϩ20 to ϩ156 region of the c-FLIP promoter with class I and class II ARE consensus sequences [CITATION_1] revealed four putative AREs within this region (Fig. 2C) . The point mutations on ARE-3, -2, -1, -2ϩ3, or -1ϩ3 decreased, but did not eliminate, AR-dependent luciferase activity ( Fig. 2A, left panel) , whereas the mutations on ARE-1ϩ2 completely abolished it. These results suggest that there are multiple AREs in the ϩ20 to ϩ156 region of the c-FLIP gene. A gel shift assay confirmed that the identified AREs were functional. Three c-FLIP AREs interacted with the DNA-binding domain (DBD) of AR (Fig. 2B) . The affinity of AR-DBD to ARE-2 and ARE-3 was similar (lanes 2-4 and lanes 6-8), but its affinity to ARE-1 was 3-fold lower (lanes 10-12 vs. lanes 2-4 and lanes [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . The mutations on the conserved bases in the ARE probes abrogated the DNA-AR-DBD complexes (lanes [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] [CITATION_9] [CITATION_10] [CITATION_11] [CITATION_12] [CITATION_13] , confirming the specificity of the observed interactions of AR-DBD with the c-FLIP AREs. We have not yet tested the putative c-FLIP ARE-4 by the above analyses. Thus, the identified functional c-FLIP AREs lie within the region of ϩ50 to ϩ150, and this region and the region (Ϫ321 to Ϫ32) amplified by PCR in the ChIP assay could be in the same DNA fragments (average size of 1 kb) immunopurified by anti-AR antibody (Fig. 1B,  lanes 5 and 6) .",
